{"id":409,"category_slug":"english-conversations","category_name":"Conversations","position":11,"title":"11. What's A Grant?","subtitle":"","level":"A2","parts":11,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant.409/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/0-11-whats-a-grant.mp3","transcript":"My daughter is going to college.\nThat's great, but it must be expensive.\nYes, but she has a grant.\nA grant? What's a grant?\nThe government is giving her money.\nTo pay for her education?\nThat's right.\nDoes it pay for everything?\nNo, she has a loan, too.\nWhat's the difference between a loan and a grant?\nYou have to pay back a loan; a grant is a gift.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:48:28","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"My daughter is going to college.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/1.mp3","time_start":1.82,"time_end":3.59},{"position":2,"content":"That's great, but it must be expensive.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/2.mp3","time_start":3.59,"time_end":5.5},{"position":3,"content":"Yes, but she has a grant.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/3.mp3","time_start":5.5,"time_end":7.22},{"position":4,"content":"A grant? What's a grant?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/4.mp3","time_start":7.22,"time_end":8.99},{"position":5,"content":"The government is giving her money.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/5.mp3","time_start":8.99,"time_end":10.49},{"position":6,"content":"To pay for her education?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/6.mp3","time_start":10.49,"time_end":11.9},{"position":7,"content":"That's right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/7.mp3","time_start":11.9,"time_end":12.55},{"position":8,"content":"Does it pay for everything?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/8.mp3","time_start":12.61,"time_end":13.77},{"position":9,"content":"No, she has a loan, too.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/9.mp3","time_start":13.77,"time_end":15.69},{"position":10,"content":"What's the difference between a loan and a grant?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/10.mp3","time_start":15.73,"time_end":18.17},{"position":11,"content":"You have to pay back a loan; a grant is a gift.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/11-whats-a-grant-2022-03-07-20-54-47/11.mp3","time_start":18.17,"time_end":21.37}]}